 as the high-turnover items such as shampoo and dish detergent are the type=
 of nondiscretionary goods the consumer requires immediately. Until relativ=
ely recently, Amazon was unable to fully knock the $700B category from its =
perch, despite a lower-priced selection for the consumer, as the product of=
fering did not address the time-sensitive demands=E2=80=A6

The retail offerings from Walgreens and CVS had previously avoided the fate=
 of peers with relatively stable growth. Their retail businesses suffered f=
rom a decline in foot traffic during the pandemic and sales recovered in 20=
21 with double-digit growth into early 2022, boosted by OTC test kits and t=
he reopening. After lapping the easy comps, growth peaked in early 2022, ev=
entually decelerating to Y/Y declines. Even after adjusting for store closu=
res, same-store sales were negative for both companies. For Walgreens=E2=80=
=99 U.S. retail stores, Y/Y declines started in 3QCY22 with the headwinds r=
eaching CVS by 2QCY23. Walgreens and CVS have now declined for six and four=
 consecutive quarters, respectively.

